117 4. (1) There is hereby created in the state treasury
118 the "Commercial Sexual Exploitation of Children Education
119 and Awareness Fund", which shall consist of moneys
120 appropriated to it by the general assembly and any grants,
121 gifts, donations, and bequests. The state treasurer shall
122 be custodian of the fund. In accordance with sections
123 30.170 and 30.180, the state treasurer shall approve
124 disbursements as required by the attorney general. The fund
125 shall be a dedicated fund and, upon appropriation, moneys in
126 this fund shall be used to pay for the position of the
127 executive director and for administrative support of the
128 statewide council against adult trafficking and the
129 commercial exploitation of children, education and awareness
130 regarding human trafficking, and anti-trafficking efforts
131 throughout the state of Missouri.
132 (2) Notwithstanding the provisions of section 33.080
133 to the contrary, any moneys remaining in the fund at the end
134 of the biennium shall not revert to the credit of the
135 general revenue fund.
29

136 (3) The state treasurer shall invest moneys in the
137 fund in the same manner as other funds are invested. Any
138 interest and moneys earned on such investments shall be
139 credited to the fund.
140 5. There is hereby established the "Committee on Sex
141 and Human Trafficking Training" within the council.
142 6. The committee shall consist of the following
143 members:
144 (1) A representative of the attorney general's office
145 who is involved in the office's anti-trafficking efforts
146 appointed by the attorney general;
147 (2) A representative of the department of public
148 safety with experience in human trafficking investigations
149 appointed by the director of the department of public safety;
150 (3) A representative from a child advocacy center
151 appointed by the director of a statewide nonprofit
152 organization that advocates for the protection of children;
153 (4) A juvenile officer appointed by the chief justice
154 of the supreme court of Missouri;
155 (5) A representative from an agency providing victim
156 services appointed by the director of the department of
157 social services;
158 (6) A representative from a child abuse medical
159 resource center, as defined in section 334.950, appointed by
160 the director of the department of health and senior services;
161 (7) The executive director of the Missouri office of
162 prosecution services or his or her designee; and
163 (8) A representative from a statewide organization of
164 nurses or emergency nurses.
165 7. The member who represents the attorney general's
166 office shall serve as chair of the committee.
167 8. Members of the committee shall serve without
168 compensation but may be reimbursed for actual expenses
30

169 necessary to the performance of their official duties for
170 the committee.
171 9. The committee shall annually evaluate, and
172 establish guidelines for, the sex and human trafficking
173 training required under sections 56.265, 190.142, 211.326,
174 337.618, and 590.050. The committee shall produce, and
175 distribute in a digital platform, training that meets its
176 guidelines. The committee may approve training produced by
177 other entities as consistent with its guidelines.
178 10. Any board, department, or agency that regulates
179 any profession for which sex and human trafficking training
180 is required as described in subsection 9 of this section may
181 provide such training. Funding for the training shall be
182 subject to appropriations.
183 11. The provisions of subsections 5 to 10 of this
184 section shall become effective on January 1, 2027, and shall
185 expire on December 31, 2031.
