1 566.151. 1. This section shall be known and may be
2 cited as "Evie and Sophie's Law".
3 2. For purposes of this section, "minor" means a
4 person under eighteen years of age.
5 3. A person [twenty-one years of age or older] commits
6 the offense of grooming or enticement of a [child] minor if,
7 being more than four years older than a minor, he or she
8 knowingly, by any means or through any pattern of conduct,
9 attempts to persuade, solicit, coax, entice, or lure or
10 persuades, solicits, coaxes, entices, or lures [whether by
11 words, actions or through communication via the internet or
12 any electronic communication, any person who is less than
13 seventeen years of age for the purpose of engaging in sexual
14 conduct] such minor with the intent to prepare, condition,
15 manipulate, or otherwise cause such minor to engage in
16 sexual conduct, a sexual performance, or a commercial sex
17 act.
18 [2.] 4. It is not a defense to a prosecution for a
19 violation of this section that the [other] person believed
20 to be a minor was a peace officer masquerading as a minor.
74

21 [3.] 5. Grooming or enticement of a [child or an
22 attempt to commit enticement of a child] minor is a felony
23 for which the authorized term of imprisonment shall be not
24 less than five years and not more than thirty years, unless
25 the grooming or enticement results in the minor engaging in
26 sexual conduct, a sexual performance, or a commercial sex
27 act, in which case the minimum authorized term of
28 imprisonment shall be not less than ten years. No person
29 convicted and sentenced to the department of corrections
30 under this section shall be eligible for parole[,
31 probation,] or conditional release[, or suspended imposition
32 or execution of sentence] for a period of five calendar
33 years, unless the grooming or enticement results in the
34 minor engaging in sexual conduct, a sexual performance, or a
35 commercial sex act, in which case the person shall not be
36 eligible for parole, probation, conditional release, or
37 suspended imposition or execution of sentence for a period
38 of ten calendar years. Upon conviction, the punishment
39 imposed under this subsection shall be in addition and
40 consecutive to any punishment provided by law for any crime
41 committed as a result of the offense committed under this
42 section.
43 6. Notwithstanding the provisions of sections 557.011,
44 558.019, and 559.021 to the contrary, a person found guilty
45 of violating this section shall be ordered by the sentencing
46 court to pay restitution to the victim of the offense. The
47 minimum restitution ordered by the court for such victim
48 shall be in the amount determined by the court necessary to
49 compensate the victim for the mental and physical
50 rehabilitation of the victim, any lost income or educational
51 disruption, or relocation or housing assistance for the
52 victim.
