101 official.
102 3. The registration requirements of sections 589.400
103 through 589.425 shall be as provided under subsection 4 of
104 this section unless:
105 (1) All offenses requiring registration are reversed,
106 vacated, or set aside;
107 (2) The registrant is no longer required to register
108 and his or her name shall be removed from the registry under
109 the provisions of section 589.414; or
110 (3) The court orders the removal or exemption of such
111 person from the registry under section 589.401.
112 4. The registration requirements shall be as follows:
113 (1) Fifteen years if the offender is a tier I sex
114 offender as provided under section 589.414;
115 (2) Twenty-five years if the offender is a tier II sex
116 offender as provided under section 589.414; or
117 (3) The life of the offender if the offender is a tier
118 III sex offender.
119 5. (1) The registration period shall be reduced as
120 described in subdivision (3) of this subsection for a sex
121 offender who maintains a clean record for the periods
122 described under subdivision (2) of this subsection by:
105

123 (a) Not being adjudicated of any offense for which
124 imprisonment for more than one year may be imposed;
125 (b) Not being adjudicated of any sex offense;
126 (c) Successfully completing any periods of supervised
127 release, probation, or parole; and
128 (d) Successfully completing an appropriate sex
129 offender treatment program certified by the attorney general.
130 (2) In the case of a:
131 (a) Tier I sex offender, the period during which the
132 clean record shall be maintained is ten years;
133 (b) Tier III sex offender adjudicated delinquent for
134 the offense which required registration in a sex offender
135 registry under sections 589.400 to 589.425, the period
136 during which the clean record shall be maintained is twenty-
137 five years.
138 (3) In the case of a:
139 (a) Tier I sex offender, the reduction is five years;
140 (b) Tier III sex offender adjudicated delinquent, the
141 reduction is from life to that period for which the clean
142 record under paragraph (b) of subdivision (2) of this
143 subsection is maintained.
144 6. For processing an initial sex offender registration
